.TH "snd_pcm_hw_params_choose" 9 "snd_pcm_hw_params_choose" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_hw_params_choose \- choose a configuration defined by @params
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_pcm_hw_params_choose
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *pcm "  ","
.BI "struct snd_pcm_hw_params *params "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pcm" 12
PCM instance
.IP "params" 12
the hw_params instance
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Choose one configuration from configuration space defined by \fIparams\fP.
The configuration chosen is that obtained fixing in this order:
first access, first format, first subformat, min channels,
min rate, min period time, max buffer size, min tick time
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful, or a negative error code on failure.
